  "prompt": "What does it feel like to overhear somebody talk behind your back?",
  "response": "Overhearing someone talk behind your back can evoke a range of emotions. Many people might feel hurt or betrayed, especially if the conversation involves negative comments or criticism. It can lead to feelings of insecurity, anxiety, or self-doubt, questioning the nature of relationships and how others perceive them. \n\nSome might feel anger or frustration, particularly if the remarks are unfounded or misleading. In contrast, others may brush it off and feel indifferent, seeing it as a reflection of the other person's character rather than their own worth. Overall, the experience can be quite uncomfortable and can impact one's sense of trust and connection with others.",
